&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://wonderschool.com/&quot;&gt;Wonderschool&lt;/a&gt; is harnessing the power of technology to provide comprehensive support to child care providers operating out of their homes as well as in the government and non-profit sectors. Our products enable child care providers to create high-quality environments and meet the demands of their business, while also helping parents in need of childcare solutions through the creation of an accessible marketplace.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Head of State Government Sales who is a first-principles thinker with a proven track record in government sales. San Francisco is preferred, but we will consider exceptional candidates anywhere in the US. This role reports directly to the CEO.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wonderschool already has active partnerships across 15 states and a very rich pipeline. This is not a build-from-scratch role - you’re coming in to scale what’s already working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a 9-to-5 job. It requires a significant amount of travel - you will attend events throughout the country, work alongside marketing to generate leads and attract the full funnel, and personally carry a bag while building and leading a sales team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$450,000 OTE + equity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership of a well-defined, proven sales playbook and scale it across states, cities, and counties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run meetings, develop pipeline, and own go-to-market strategy for government sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sell - this is a player-coach role; a significant portion of your time will be in front of customers closing deals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hire, coach, and develop a high-performing sales team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with marketing to drive event presence, lead generation, and top-of-funnel pipeline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI tools to accelerate outreach, communications, and pipeline management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with key government stakeholders - agencies, elected officials, regulators, and associations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop data-driven forecasts and report pipeline health and learnings to leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Refine deal desk, sales qualification, and process as we grow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A first-principles thinker who doesn’t just follow playbooks - you understand &lt;em&gt;why&lt;/em&gt; they work and know how to adapt&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven government sales background with experience closing SaaS-based contracts with state, city, or county agencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated track record closing $1M–$15M+ ARR deals with government entities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep familiarity with government procurement processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced team leader and recruiter who can attract and develop great salespeople&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly data-driven with a bias toward accountability and measurable outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable with significant travel and an events-heavy calendar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ready to work with and maximize AI-powered tools for outreach and communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced enough to operate independently, but hungry enough to still love selling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll have strong support from the CEO, a clear playbook, and existing momentum across 15 states. The opportunity to build something meaningful is real. We want someone experienced, energized, and ready to scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time role, 5-6 days a week, with significant travel and an events-heavy calendar.&lt;/p&gt;

